at is is atman (Self). Ocean is permanent =\r\nand still, but ripples that arise in it are transient and moving. But rippl=\r\nes are part of ocean only and you do not start labeling ripples as &quot;no=\r\nn-ocean&quot;.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; s=\r\nize=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=\r\n=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Atman or Purusha or Shiva is the p=\r\notential energy of this cosmos, while Maya or Prakriti or Shakti is the kin=\r\netic energy of this cosmos. Shiva and Shakti are seen as different entities=\r\n by some people, but rishis have declared their oneness. Potential energy b=\r\necomes kinetic energy and vice versa.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;f=\r\nont color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div ali=\r\ngn=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Atman is th=\r\ne still ocean and Maya is the force (kinetic) that gives rise to moving rip=\r\nples on the surface. A ripple that exerts itself to move in a particular wa=\r\ny keeps colliding with the force and keeps moving hither and tither in a ch=\r\naotic way for a very long time. A ripple that does not exert itself and mov=\r\nes smoothly as dictated by the force will eventually grind to a halt and ce=\r\nase to exist as a ripple on the surface. It then becomes part of the still =\r\nocean. If a ripple exerts itself to become still, it may even take longer t=\r\no become still. What prolongs a ripple is not movement but resisting the di=\r\nrection given by the force and exerting to move in a particular way (or eve=\r\nn exerting to become still). A ripple that surrenders to the force will rid=\r\ne the course and die down faster.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font =\r\ncolor=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=\r\n=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Contemplate t=\r\nhe imagery I presented above regarding Atman and Maya, ignorant/egoistic ac=\r\ntion and detached action! It is very apt.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;=\r\n&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div a=\r\nlign=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;*=A0=A0=\r\n=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;=\r\nfont color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div al=\r\nign=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;In not-so-=\r\ndistant past, sannyasins remained in ashrams and isolated themselves from s=\r\nociety and did their sadhana. Swami Vivekananda started a new trend.&lt;/font&gt;=\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Ver=\r\ndana&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;=\r\n2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;A sannyasin renounces expectation of things from people=\r\n stuck in transient material world and does not depend on anyone. But he ma=\r\ny still *give* basic material things to those hapless people stuck in trans=\r\nient material world! For example, Swami Vivekananda and his brother monks w=\r\nent to places struck by plague, floods, droughts, cyclones etc and served p=\r\neople. They provided food, medicines etc (instead of lecturing that body is=\r\n a transient illusion and one should stop worrying about its welfare!) and =\r\nalso did construction work. They ignored the welfare of their own bodies, p=\r\nut themselves at risk and overcame maya personally. But they served those s=\r\ntill stuck in maya without looking down upon them or their needs or maya th=\r\nat trapped them! Those who wanted food got food, those who wanted medicines=\r\n got medicines and those who wanted books got books. Renunciation means you=\r\n do not expect anything from anyone and accept whatever comes to you natura=\r\nlly. It does not necessarily mean rejecting or ignoring others. Overcoming =\r\nmaya does not require belittling maya or belittling those still stuck in ma=\r\nya.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; f=\r\nace=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000=\r\n&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;The trend started by Swami Vivekananda was co=\r\nntinued by Swami Sivananda. For that reason, it is a bit weird to see him t=\r\nalking so ill of action! He was obviously trying to inspire a specific grou=\r\np of people for a specific body of work. These words are neither universal =\r\nnor do they reflect his tremendous wisdom I have seen elsewhere!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/di=\r\nv&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana=\r\n&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; f=\r\nace=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div=\r\n&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=\r\n=A0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; fac=\r\ne=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;All this intellectual discussion may be satisfying to some, b=\r\nut the quote from Swami Brahmanananda in the other mail is very apt: &quot;=\r\nYou have been only hearing of all these spiritual things. Now realise them.=\r\n You have done enough study and reasoning. Now do some spiritual practice. =\r\nFirst take up that aspect of God which appeals to you most. Follow your own=\r\n path of Sadhana. When you realise God through it, you will feel the joy of=\r\n realising Him also in other aspects and through other paths.&quot;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;=\r\n/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verd=\r\nana&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2=\r\n&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;According to Ramakrishna, Swami Brahmananda was a gopala=\r\n who accompanied Lord Krishna in a previous life. His words are simple, pra=\r\ngmatic and powerful.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000=\r\n000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font=\r\n color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;I want this forum to facilit=\r\nate exchange of Vedic knowledge (and I will also be contributing, though in=\r\n spurts). But I want more that this forum should inspire people to do sadha=\r\nna and find God. In the end, that is what matters.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div alig=\r\nn=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/=\r\ndiv&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&